{"id":29504578136,"name":"Test","node_id":"WFR_kwLOA_1uaM8AAAAG3pwiWA","head_branch":"fix_l2_cache_2.42.5.1","head_sha":"0a636993d8cd05b847fe0109d96a27771117fa6b","path":".github/workflows/run-tests.yml","run_number":54776,"run_attempt":1,"event":"pull_request","display_title":"perf: store Hibernate L2 cache entries by reference (IdentityCopier)","status":"completed","conclusion":"failure","workflow_id":10954,"check_suite_id":79885112695,"check_suite_node_id":"CS_kwDOA_1uaM8AAAASmYYVdw","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/29504578136","html_url":"https://github.com/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/29504578136","pull_requests":[{"id":4069243866,"number":24471,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/pulls/24471","head":{"ref":"fix_l2_cache_2.42.5.1","sha":"0a636993d8cd05b847fe0109d96a27771117fa6b","repo":{"id":66940520,"name":"dhis2-core","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core"}},"base":{"ref":"patch/2.42.5.1","sha":"65a70b8187ec52dcd85e4587372f8b8820489376","repo":{"id":66940520,"name":"dhis2-core","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core"}}}],"created_at":"2026-07-16T13:59:30Z","updated_at":"2026-07-16T14:14:45Z","run_started_at":"2026-07-16T13:59:30Z","jobs_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/29504578136/jobs","logs_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/29504578136/logs","check_suite_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/check-suites/79885112695","artifacts_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/29504578136/artifacts","cancel_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/29504578136/cancel","rerun_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/29504578136/rerun","head_commit":{"message":"perf: store Hibernate L2 cache entries by reference (IdentityCopier)\n\nThe Ehcache 3.12 bump (#23834 / #24002) switched the on-heap L2 store to the\nJSR-107 store-by-value default, implemented by SerializingCopier: a full Java\nserialize/deserialize round-trip on every cache get and putFromLoad. Profiling a\nproduction tracker import (DHIS2-21800) showed this dominates: ~50% of the thread\nprofile serializing entities under the AbstractReadWriteAccess ReentrantReadWriteLock\n(READ_WRITE strategy), manifesting as long \"waited\" time (park on the lock, not\nblocked) and heavy transient allocation that drives frequent young-gen GC; it also\nmade requests hold their DB connection for the whole duration, draining the pool.\n\nConfigure an explicit IdentityCopier on defaultCacheTemplate so the mapped entity\nand query regions store by reference, overriding the JSR-107 by-value semantics\n(Ehcache logs \"overwriting JSR-107 by-value semantics\"). This restores the pre-3.12\n(Ehcache 2.x) behaviour and eliminates the redundant copy: Hibernate's L2 contract\nalready isolates callers at the type level - entity CacheEntry state is deep-copied\non disassemble/assemble (e.g. JsonBinaryType.assemble -\u003e deepCopy) and all immutable\ncustom UserTypes share safely.\n\nAdd EhcacheStoreByReferenceTest, which loads the real ehcache.xml through the JSR-107\npath (as JCacheRegionFactory does, storeByValue=true) and asserts a get returns the\nsame instance that was put. Update CachedEntityJsonbSerializableTest's Javadoc: the\nSerializable requirement still holds (UserType#disassemble returns Serializable and\nHibernate stores a Serializable[]), and that test keeps running store-by-value via an\nempty cache config, so it remains a strict guard.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e","author":{"name":"Enrico","email":"enrico@dhis2.org"},"id":"0a636993d8cd05b847fe0109d96a27771117fa6b","tree_id":"08b2042795e773eb5b043182dd047eb29a3ce871","timestamp":"2026-07-16T13:58:53Z","committer":{"name":"Enrico","email":"enrico@dhis2.org"}},"workflow_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/workflows/10954","repositor